Step Up Nigeria, an NGO, has launched a programme aimed at promoting integrity and raising awareness on the need to eradicate corruption through parents by inculcating a culture of integrity from the formative years of their children. The Executive Director of Strep Up Nigeria, Mrs Onyinye Ough, who disclosed this in Abuja, announced that the theme: “Parents Anti-Corruption Champion Initiative”, was focused on taking critical actions against corrupt practices commencing from homes. Mrs Ough, explained that the project was part of their effort through the Catch Them Young Initiative, focused on using creative techniques and storytelling approaches to educate young Nigerians on the meaning of corruption and its impact on society. 